# Town of Wiley Core Workflow Rules

## Project Context
- Angular 21 standalone components, signals-first (input/output/computed/inject), OnPush change detection, native control flow (@if/@for/@switch), reactive forms.
- Strict WCAG AA accessibility, semantic HTML, PrimeNG + SCSS.
- Prefer MCP tools from [`.cursor/mcp.json`](../.cursor/mcp.json) in Cursor and [`.vscode/mcp.json`](../.vscode/mcp.json) in VS Code: **angular-cli**, **primeng**, **playwright-test** (`run-test-mcp-server`), **microsoft/playwright-mcp**, and **cursor-ide-browser** (when enabled) for Angular/PrimeNG/Playwright guidance before generic knowledge.
- Use repo-local files: .instructions.md, .github/skills/TownOfWiley-Dev/SKILL.md, .github/instructions/*.instructions.md.

## Mandatory Practices
- **Angular**: Standalone APIs, signals, OnPush, native control flow over *ngIf etc. Avoid ngClass/ngStyle; use [class] and [style] bindings. Keep templates semantic and accessible.
- **Changes**: Minimal, match existing src/ patterns and structure. Consult MCP before editing.
- **Formatting & Quality**: Run Trunk (trunk check --fix) before commits. Use existing npm scripts for test/build/lint.
- **Secrets & AI**: Use `npm run secrets:*` scripts. Never commit credentials. For AI features, server-side boundaries, graceful degradation, validate outputs.
- **Testing**: Follow Playwright standards - user-facing locators (getByRole, getByLabel), isolated tests, fixtures.
- **Git**: Feature branches, only deployable to main. 

## Always:
- Review .vscode/settings.json, tasks.json, extensions.json for workspace config.
- For Angular tasks start with Angular CLI MCP where possible.
- Bilingual English/Spanish where UI text appears (use i18n patterns).

Follow these before any code changes.
